From: Kairo Authors <kairo@research>
Date: Wed Jun 24 19:00:00 2026 +0000
Subject: [RFC/POC] 0028: recompute-aware eviction scheduler scaffold

RFC/POC — Not for LKML submission.

Add a conceptual eviction-class model and eviction-scoring scaffold that
prioritises eviction of recomputable, short-lived cache data over
non-recomputable, model-local, or persistent data.

AI KV-cache regions have distinct recompute costs and lifetime classes.
A generic block-layer eviction policy should prefer to evict:

  1. recomputable short-lived data  (cheapest to reconstruct)
  2. ephemeral prefetch cache       (speculative, low cost)
  3. recomputable session cache     (moderate cost)
  4. ordinary session cache         (session-scoped)
  5. model-local cache              (expensive to reconstruct)
  6. persistent / durable data      (never evict unless forced)

This patch adds:

  enum kairo_eviction_class
    KAIRO_EVICT_NONE
    KAIRO_EVICT_RECOMPUTABLE_SHORT
    KAIRO_EVICT_RECOMPUTABLE_SESSION
    KAIRO_EVICT_EPHEMERAL_PREFETCH
    KAIRO_EVICT_SESSION_CACHE
    KAIRO_EVICT_MODEL_CACHE
    KAIRO_EVICT_PERSISTENT_AVOID

  struct kairo_eviction_decision
    eviction_class, model_id, session_id, cache_pool_id,
    placement_group, recompute_ok, ephemeral, persistent_avoid,
    discard_preferred, writeback_required, score, reason_flags

Conceptual helpers:

  kairo_eviction_class_from_request(struct request *rq)
  kairo_eviction_score_request(struct request *rq)
  kairo_should_prioritize_eviction(struct request *rq)
  kairo_should_defer_eviction(struct request *rq)
  kairo_account_eviction_decision(
      struct request *rq,
      const struct kairo_eviction_decision *decision)

Eviction score policy (higher = safer eviction candidate):

   recomputable short-lived cache       +100
   ephemeral prefetch cache             +90
   recomputable session cache           +80
   ordinary session cache               +50
   model-local cache                    +20
   persistent / durable data            -1000
   decode-hot data                      -500
   recently accessed data               -100

All helpers are static inline __maybe_unused no-ops in this patch.
No dispatch path calls them.

Sysfs counters (defined but not wired to any kobject):

   kairo_eviction_decisions
   kairo_eviction_recomputable_short
   kairo_eviction_recomputable_session
   kairo_eviction_ephemeral_prefetch
   kairo_eviction_session_cache
   kairo_eviction_model_cache
   kairo_eviction_persistent_avoided
   kairo_eviction_decode_hot_deferred
   kairo_eviction_discard_preferred
   kairo_eviction_writeback_required

CONCEPTUAL-HOOK: No dispatch-path integration, no sysfs registration,
no runtime eviction decisions.  The eviction scoring and class model
are defined for RFC review and benchmark-driven policy exploration.

LINUX-6.8-CHECK:
  block/blk-mq.c:          blk_mq_rq_ctx_init, blk_mq_dispatch_rq
  block/blk-core.c:        generic_make_request
  include/linux/blk-mq.h:  struct request (no kairo_hints field)
  mm/page-writeback.c:     writeback vs discard decision path

Signed-off-by: Kairo Authors <kairo@research>
---
 include/linux/blk-mq.h | 243 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 block/blk-mq.c         |  73 +++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 314 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/include/linux/blk-mq.h b/include/linux/blk-mq.h
index e9f0a1b..c3d4e5f 100755
--- a/include/linux/blk-mq.h
+++ b/include/linux/blk-mq.h
@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@
 /* SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0 */
 /*
- * Copyright (C) 2024 Kairo Authors
